
GSR sensor - electrical resistance of the skin

a braslet witch contains a sensor to track the skinpressur (like a lie detector principle) triggers several little vibration motors around the user's wrist
(https://www.instructables.com/Arduino-Emotion-Stress-Tester-%E6%AA%A2%E6%B8%AC%E6%83%85%E7%B7%92%E7%9A%84%E5%A3%93%E5%8A%9B%E6%84%9F%E6%B8%AC%E5%99%A8/)


Stuff I'll need: 

skinpressur sensor:
https://www.reichelt.de/arduino-gsr-sensor-grv-gsr-sens-p191210.html?&nbc=1

prototyping vibration motor: 
https://www.reichelt.de/arduino-vibrationsmotor-grv-vibration-p191165.html?&trstct=pos_0&nbc=1

4x vibration sensors:
https://www.reichelt.de/dc-vibrationsmotor-3v-80ma-10000rpm-eku-vm1002a3-0-p330549.html?&trstct=pos_2&nbc=1

